Buuilding classification and Transfer Learning models on Custom Datasets¶

  1. Using a simple classifier model the accuracy doesn't improve after a point.
  2. Tried increasing the no. of layers, filters, dropout
  3. Also tried Data augmentation
  4. Transfer learning gives better accuracy - VGG model has a very satble training as compared to Imagenet

#Saving images and labels in dataset

labels = ['cats','dogs']
img_size = 150
def get_data(dir_path):
    data = []
    for _label in labels:
#         print(_label)
        sub_dir = os.path.join(dir_path,_label)
        for imgname in os.listdir(sub_dir):
            image = cv2.imread(os.path.join(sub_dir,imgname))[...,::-1]
            if image.shape != (150,150,3):
                #print('Changing shape of ', imgname, image.shape)
                image = cv2.resize(image, (img_size, img_size))
            label = labels.index(_label)
            data.append([image, label])
    return data

train_data = get_data(train_dir_path)
test_data = get_data(validation_dir_path)

# Building model

model = Sequential()
model.add(Conv2D(32,3,padding= 'same', activation='relu', input_shape = (150,150,3)))
model.add(MaxPool2D())
# model.add(Normalization())
model.add(Conv2D(64,3,padding= 'same', activation='relu'))
model.add(MaxPool2D())
# model.add(Normalization())
model.add(Conv2D(128,3,padding= 'same', activation='relu'))
model.add(MaxPool2D())
# model.add(Normalization())
model.add(Dropout(0.3))
model.add(Flatten())
model.add(Dense(128, activation= 'relu'))
model.add(Dense(1, activation= 'sigmoid'))
model.summary()

opt = Adam(lr = 0.01)
model.compile(optimizer=opt, loss = tf.keras.losses.BinaryCrossentropy(from_logits= True), metrics=['accuracy'])
history = model.fit(x_train ,y_train,epochs = 50 , validation_data = (x_valid, y_valid))

# model.add(Normalization())

model.add(MaxPool2D())

model.add(Conv2D(128,3,padding= 'same', activation='relu'))
model.add(MaxPool2D())

model.add(MaxPool2D())
# model.add(Normalization())
model.add(Dropout(0.3))

model.summary()
